{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_69","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,200p' ISSUE_COMMENTS.md && sed -n '1,260p' PR_COMMENTS.md\"","aggregated_output":"Changes committed in PR #<NN>.\n\nAdded the two requested biological process terms for issues #31936 and #31937:\n\n- `GO:0140422` symbiont-mediated suppression of host immunothrombosis\n- `GO:0140424` symbiont-mediated activation of blood coagulation, intrinsic pathway\n\nFull ontology validation passed after the edits.\n## Summary\n\nAdded two new biological process terms requested by PR #32031:\n\n- `GO:0140422` symbiont-mediated suppression of host immunothrombosis\n- `GO:0140424` symbiont-mediated activation of blood coagulation, intrinsic pathway\n\nBoth terms include definitions with validated PMID provenance, term tracker links to the originating requests, and new-term metadata using `created_by: dragon-ai-agent`.\n\n## Rationale\n\n`GO:0140424` follows the existing symbiont-mediated activation design pattern:\n\n```obo\nintersection_of: GO:0044003 ! symbiont-mediated perturbation of host process\nintersection_of: positively_regulates_in_another_organism GO:0007597 ! blood coagulation, intrinsic pathway\n```\n\n`GO:0140422` was placed under `GO:0052031 ! symbiont-mediated perturbation of host defense response`. I did not add an `intersection_of` logical definition for this term because the local ontology does not currently have a host immunothrombosis biological process term to use as a precise target, and using an approximate target would over-specify the class.\n\n## Research And Reference Validation\n\nI validated all definition PMIDs using `linkml-reference-validator cache reference` and recorded supporting excerpts in `RESEARCH.md`. The support text validation passed for all six PMIDs:\n\n- `PMID:24278414`\n- `PMID:40973015`\n- `PMID:42049611`\n- `PMID:17142774`\n- `PMID:24910020`\n- `PMID:29619369`\n\n## Validation\n\n- Pre-change validation: `cd src/ontology && make travis_build` passed.\n- Post-change validation: `cd src/ontology && make travis_build` passed.\n- Reference support validation: `linkml-reference-validator validate text-file -r 'SUPPORT: (\\S+:\\S+) \"(.*)\"' -t 2 -R 1 RESEARCH.md` passed.\n\n## Checklist\n\n- [x] PLAN: Issue context was analyzed. The imported issue context was sparse, so the linked upstream PR and referenced issues #31936/#31937 were used to infer the requested local change.\n- [x] PRE-VALIDATION: Current ontology validated before edits.\n- [x] RESEARCH: Background literature was checked and `RESEARCH.md` was created.\n- [x] TERM-SEARCH: Existing GO terms and relevant precedents were checked with `obo-grep.pl`.\n- [x] DESIGN-PATTERNS: Relevant symbiont-mediated host process patterns were checked and `DESIGN_PATTERNS.md` was created.\n- [x] EDITS: New terms were staged through a `terms/` file and checked into `src/ontology/go-edit.obo` with `obo-checkin.pl`.\n- [x] RELATIONSHIPS: Parentage and logical axioms were reviewed against existing precedent.\n- [x] SPECIALIZED-EDITS: N/A; no obsoletion, CHEBI chemical entity edit, catalytic activity, mapping, or taxon constraint edit was required.\n- [x] METADATA: Required IDs, names, namespaces, definitions, term tracker links, `created_by`, and `creation_date` are present.\n- [x] AUTOMATED-VALIDATION: Full `make travis_build` passed after edits.\n- [x] REFERENCE-VALIDATION: All introduced PMIDs were validated and support text was checked.\n- [x] CHANGES-COMMITTED: `src/ontology/go-edit.obo` was committed locally.\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
